        <abstract> 
<p>Young Belgian students [L. A. Errera and Gustave Gevaert] ask CD to read their paper, which summarises <hi rend="italic">Cross and self-fertilisation</hi>. They criticise CD’s views on the comparative effects of crossing flowers on the same stem and fertilisation of a flower by its own pollen ["Sur la structure et les modes de fécondation des fleurs", <hi rend="italic">Bull. Soc. Bot. Belg.</hi> 17 (1878): 38–181, 182–248].</p> 
        </abstract>
